## Content Guidelines

### Must Include

- Clear value proposition in first 3 seconds
- Role hierarchy: Thoughtworks (primary) â†’ KaiNext (secondary)
- Founder-led positioning explicitly stated
- Impact framing for featured work (verifiable metrics or scale language only)
- Production proof (real systems, real users - use scale language if metrics not verifiable)
- Clear CTAs for different user types
- Canonical title: "Founder & Principal Engineer" (KaiNext)

### Must Avoid

- Team signals ("team", "consultants", "experts" plural)
- Tool-heavy language in main sections
- Resume-style headers ("Current focus:", "Key responsibilities:")
- First-person plural ("we", "our") in delivery contexts
- Unverifiable claims ("forefront", "industry-leading")
- Corporate clichÃ©s ("transform", "revolutionize")
- Defensive language
- Visual clutter (too many badges, overwhelming stats)
- Information density that prevents scanning

### Language Guidelines

- Use operating contexts instead of tool names: "platform engineering at enterprise scale" not "Terraform Cloud and GCP"
- Focus on impact and execution, not just capabilities
- Write for scannability: key messages in first 30 seconds
- Use plain sentences, no em dashes
- Maintain factual, authoritative tone throughout
- Ensure KaiNext remains scoped, quiet, and execution-focused

